{
  "doc_id": "60888",
  "text": "Since the report describing SCD, several candidate genes affecting fatty acid composition have been identified. Sterol regulatory element binding protein1 (SREBP-1) regulates gene transcription activation by binding sequences contained in the promoters of downstream genes, including the SCD gene, to the sterol regulatory element [CITATION_1] . The intron poly morphism of SREBP-1 also affects the fatty acid composition in bovine adipose tissue [CITATION_2] . Bovine fatty acid synthase (FASN) generates a multifunctional enzyme that regulates de novo biosynthesis of longchain fatty acids in mammals [CITATION_3] . Abe et al [CITATION_4] revealed that the FASN genotypes significantly affect ed the fatty acid composition of dorsal, intramuscular, and intermuscular fat in an F 2 population generated from Japanese Black and Limousin cattle.",
